Expression strings with escaped backslashes (\\) fail to parse

Strings like "path\\to\\file" contain sequences like \t and \f that get
misinterpreted somewhere in the parsing pipeline, causing "Zig code not
allowed in flows" errors.

Fix: Need to properly handle escape sequences in the lexer's string tracking,
or ensure backslashes are preserved through the pipeline.

Low priority - escaped quotes work, which covers most use cases.
